summary:
Working out roadmaps for the IT landscape starts with thorough understanding of the business strategy. But the real challenge is to realize it step by step, which I enjoy doing together with international business and IT colleagues.
As IT manager it has been great to participate in the startup of a near-shore IT development center in the Czech Republic, which provides us a strong edge building out our key strategic proposition in a fast moving world.

I have also overseen the transition to a stable PaaS provider for non-SaaS applications, as well as the implementation of Teams and Sharepoint for collaboration and communication purposes. Furthermore, I have been responsible for the monthly transition of at least one transactional or several non-transactional companies to the new ERP system. Most of these Business Units are located within the European Union. This, as all other international projects implemented Agile, ensuring quick small changes leading to the complete replacement of the legacy landscape to a state-of-the-art and well-integrated and futureproof landscape. Additionally, I have improved the security of the entire platform from a very critical state to above-average, significantly reducing the likelihood of a breach. Other achievements include the successful implementation of a WMS system with scanning capabilities and the realization of WiFi coverage for the Europark terrain of 60,000 m2 with redundant glass fiber connection from both Germany and the Netherlands- final steps to be realized the coming 2 months.

Currently, I am working on the upcoming live release of the configurator replacement, planned for November 2023, and the modernization of the workplace for the main branch, planned for September 2023, followed by one subsidiary per month. 

I believe that my experience in managing complex projects and facilitating seamless transitions between legacy and modern systems will be of great value to any organization.', 'title': 'IT Manager', 'employment_type': 'Full-time'}]}, {'company': {'id': None, 'name': 'Weekamp Deuren BV', 'logo': None, 'url': None, 'employees': {'start': None, 'end': None}}, 'date': {'start': {'month': 2, 'day': None, 'year': 2006}, 'end': {'month': 4, 'day': None, 'year': 2020}}, 'profile_positions': [{'location': 'Dedemsvaart, Nederland', 'date': {'start': {'month': 9, 'day': None, 'year': 2010}, 'end': {'month': 4, 'day': None, 'year': 2020}}, 'company': 'Weekamp Deuren BV', 'description': 'End responsible for all IT and information management teams in the Netherlands, Czechia and Indonesia.
